WEBVTT

00:17.951 --> 00:19.985
Dandy:
Bette?

00:19.987 --> 00:21.020
Dot?

00:21.022 --> 00:22.955
Here you are.

00:22.957 --> 00:25.290
You have a visitor.

00:25.292 --> 00:27.559
This young man was concerned
about your welfare.

00:27.561 --> 00:28.994
As you can see,

00:28.996 --> 00:30.562
Bette and dot
aren't prisoners,

00:30.564 --> 00:31.864
They're
our guests.

00:31.866 --> 00:34.299
They can leave
anytime they want.

00:34.301 --> 00:36.635
Is that true?

00:36.637 --> 00:38.871
We're being treated
very well, jimmy.

00:38.873 --> 00:40.672
Gloria:
When the girls first
stepped foot in our house,

00:40.674 --> 00:42.674
They were malnourished,
both body and soul.

00:42.676 --> 00:44.676
A daily regimen of
vitamins and foie gras

00:44.678 --> 00:46.245
Brought the pink
back to their pallor.

00:46.247 --> 00:48.647
Bette, dot, I
know this seems

00:48.649 --> 00:50.649
Like the life of riley now,
but trust me,

00:50.651 --> 00:51.750
This is no place for you.

00:51.752 --> 00:53.018
Because
to them,

00:53.020 --> 00:54.686
You're nothing more
than a curiosity.

00:54.688 --> 00:57.089
A freak
to gawk at.

00:57.091 --> 00:58.390
So what do you
want us to do?

00:58.392 --> 00:59.858
Go back to
the show?

00:59.860 --> 01:00.993
How is that any different?

01:00.995 --> 01:02.561
Jimmy:
Because you'd have

01:02.563 --> 01:04.596
A whole community of
people to protect you.

01:04.598 --> 01:06.031
Gloria:
Why would we harm

01:06.033 --> 01:07.166
A hair on
their heads?

01:07.168 --> 01:08.767
We paid good money
for these girls.

01:08.769 --> 01:10.002
Dandy:
Mother's right.

01:10.004 --> 01:11.036
Don't listen to a word.

01:11.038 --> 01:13.605
Everything he says
is a lie.

01:13.607 --> 01:15.174
Bette:
Jimmy, you told us

01:15.176 --> 01:17.876
You saved those kids
from the killer clown.

01:17.878 --> 01:19.445
It was dandy.

01:19.447 --> 01:22.281
He was there when
you were unconscious.

01:22.283 --> 01:24.349
He's the real hero.

01:26.920 --> 01:30.289
Dandy:
<i>Ladies and gentlemen!</i>

01:30.291 --> 01:32.291
I've always wondered

01:32.293 --> 01:34.960
How this trick was done.
Haven't you?

01:34.962 --> 01:36.462
Leave her alone!

01:36.464 --> 01:38.030
Bette...

01:38.032 --> 01:39.765
Dot...

01:40.900 --> 01:42.101
...You have to come with me.

01:42.103 --> 01:44.236
Now.
Dandy:
You don't give

01:44.238 --> 01:45.704
The orders
in this house.

01:46.706 --> 01:48.140
Dot,

01:48.142 --> 01:50.075
I know you have
mixed feelings.

01:50.077 --> 01:52.878
You're thinking of
getting the surgery,
which I'll never allow.

01:52.880 --> 01:55.080
'cause you'd never cut a girl
in half, would you, dandy?

01:55.082 --> 01:57.449
Shut up!
Stop trying to ruin everything!

01:58.651 --> 02:01.220
How do you know, dandy?

02:02.822 --> 02:04.323
About the surgery?

02:04.325 --> 02:08.193
I told you there will be
no secrets between us.

02:09.129 --> 02:11.196
You read my diary.

02:12.999 --> 02:15.767
I want to leave.

02:15.769 --> 02:16.935
She can't leave
without bette.

02:16.937 --> 02:18.170
We're in love,

02:18.172 --> 02:20.105
And love trumps everything.

02:20.107 --> 02:22.007
Jimmy:
Well, your mother said

02:22.009 --> 02:23.242
The girls could go
any time they want.

02:23.244 --> 02:24.476
Let's let them decide.

02:26.079 --> 02:28.080
Bette,

02:28.082 --> 02:29.948
I know you love me.

02:29.950 --> 02:31.250
Tell them

02:31.252 --> 02:32.985
You want to stay

02:32.987 --> 02:35.120
And live forever
in luxury with me.
(laughs)

02:35.122 --> 02:38.090
Dot:
<i>There's something wrong</i>
<i>with dandy and you know it.</i>

02:43.596 --> 02:45.497
I'm sorry.

02:46.966 --> 02:49.801
But I choose my sister,

02:49.803 --> 02:51.970
Always.

02:51.972 --> 02:55.073
We have to go.

04:26.065 --> 04:27.065
Jimmy:
<i>Testing.</i>

04:27.067 --> 04:29.568
<i>Okay, let's do this.</i>

04:29.570 --> 04:31.970
<i>One, two, three.</i>

04:31.972 --> 04:35.540
(playing nirvana's
"come as you are")

04:48.955 --> 04:51.390
¶ come as you are

04:51.392 --> 04:53.592
¶ as you were

04:53.594 --> 04:58.096
¶ as I want you to be

04:58.098 --> 05:02.567
¶ as a friend, as a friend

05:02.569 --> 05:05.003
¶ as an old enemy

05:05.005 --> 05:07.973
¶ take your time

05:07.975 --> 05:09.775
¶ hurry up

05:09.777 --> 05:11.510
¶ the choice is yours

05:11.512 --> 05:13.912
¶ don't be late

05:13.914 --> 05:15.347
¶ take a rest

05:15.349 --> 05:17.416
¶ as a friend

05:17.418 --> 05:23.922
¶ as an old memory...

05:23.924 --> 05:27.259
¶ memory, ah

05:28.261 --> 05:31.763
¶ memory, ah

05:33.333 --> 05:36.335
¶ well, I swear

05:36.337 --> 05:39.771
¶ that I don't have a gun

05:39.773 --> 05:43.442
¶ no, I don't have a gun

05:45.044 --> 05:47.279
¶

05:51.684 --> 05:53.018
Hey, uh...

05:53.020 --> 05:54.286
You seen
andy around?

05:54.288 --> 05:56.188
Not since the last time
you came by looking.

05:58.491 --> 06:00.625
Never fall in love with
a hustler. That's my advice.

06:00.627 --> 06:02.694
¶ memory, ah

06:03.830 --> 06:06.932
¶ memory, ah

06:07.967 --> 06:10.068
You keep your mouth shut!

06:14.040 --> 06:16.041
¶ and I swear

06:16.043 --> 06:21.046
¶ that I don't have a gun

06:24.083 --> 06:28.987
¶ memory, ah.

06:30.923 --> 06:33.492
(microphone whining)

06:40.032 --> 06:41.566
Truthfully? Adequate.

06:41.568 --> 06:43.068
Jimmy:
I'm not changing anything.

06:43.070 --> 06:45.237
That's the song,
that's how I'm doing it.

06:45.239 --> 06:46.772
Tonight.
Mid-show number.

06:46.774 --> 06:48.440
Ha!

06:48.442 --> 06:50.041
Do you honestly believe

06:50.043 --> 06:51.943
That I would allow you

06:51.945 --> 06:54.546
To sap the energy
of the audience? Huh?

06:54.548 --> 06:56.448
Remember to whom you speak.

06:56.450 --> 06:59.484
I know exactly
who I'm talking to!

07:02.889 --> 07:04.122
A liar.

07:04.124 --> 07:07.626
And we don't take
orders from liars.

07:11.431 --> 07:13.432
What's going on here, huh?
What is this?

07:13.434 --> 07:14.933
The twins,
elsa.

07:14.935 --> 07:16.268
We know what you
did with the twins.

07:16.270 --> 07:17.636
They ran off!

07:17.638 --> 07:18.970
I told you that.

07:18.972 --> 07:20.505
Yeah, we heard
your story.

07:21.974 --> 07:24.042
Maybe it's time
we heard theirs.

07:24.044 --> 07:25.110
What?

07:28.548 --> 07:31.883
You sold
them off.

07:31.885 --> 07:33.251
Like pets.

07:33.253 --> 07:36.154
That's not quite how
it happened, actually...

07:36.156 --> 07:37.556
Bette
<i>what are you doing?</i>

07:37.558 --> 07:38.490
Dot:
<i>Keep it buttoned.</i>

07:38.492 --> 07:39.558
<i>I know what I'm doing.</i>

07:41.127 --> 07:44.229
It's true miss elsa
took us to dandy mott,

07:44.231 --> 07:45.831
But only because I asked her to.

07:45.833 --> 07:46.965
But you said
that...

07:46.967 --> 07:48.133
Well, you misunderstood.

07:48.135 --> 07:50.702
Miss elsa
didn't sell us.

07:51.804 --> 07:53.872
She helped us.

07:55.508 --> 07:59.144
We wanted to experience
the finer things in life.

07:59.146 --> 08:00.846
And elsa

08:00.848 --> 08:03.114
Was kind enough
to make that happen.

08:03.116 --> 08:05.817
But she also said we
always had a home here,

08:05.819 --> 08:07.219
If that's what
we wanted.

08:08.521 --> 08:10.088
So we've decided to come home.

08:11.791 --> 08:14.326
If you'll have us.

08:14.328 --> 08:16.428
Well, of course, my darlings.

08:16.430 --> 08:18.697
Anything
you want.

08:31.677 --> 08:32.978
Desiree:
<i>Miss ethel,</i>

08:32.980 --> 08:34.379
We'll get this
taken care of.

08:34.381 --> 08:36.214
Don't you worry about me.

08:36.216 --> 08:38.016
The good doctor's
gonna fix me up,

08:38.018 --> 08:40.819
Right as rain.

08:40.821 --> 08:43.154
You be sure and
book your surgery.

08:43.156 --> 08:45.557
Desiree: Oh, I will.
I can hardly wait.

08:52.031 --> 08:54.232
"closed for
business"?

08:54.234 --> 08:57.269
What on earth?

09:15.021 --> 09:17.589
(door opens)

09:17.591 --> 09:19.391
Where's dr.
Bonham?

09:19.393 --> 09:22.027
He's dead.

09:22.029 --> 09:24.162
Oh, no...

09:24.164 --> 09:25.597
Spare me
the theatrics.

09:25.599 --> 09:27.332
I'm not a fan of yours.

09:27.334 --> 09:29.334
Well, you're a very
rude young woman.

09:29.336 --> 09:30.769
Who are you?

09:30.771 --> 09:31.703
I'm his daughter.

09:31.705 --> 09:33.004
Oh, you're the one

09:33.006 --> 09:34.005
He moved down here for?

09:34.007 --> 09:36.074
No.

09:36.076 --> 09:37.375
I'm the other one.

09:37.377 --> 09:39.544
The one without
a husband and children.

09:39.546 --> 09:41.880
I came down from boston
to bury him.

09:41.882 --> 09:43.949
What happened to him?

09:43.951 --> 09:46.117
You killed him!

09:46.119 --> 09:47.919
Your very existence

09:47.921 --> 09:50.188
Challenged his beliefs
in god and science.

09:50.190 --> 09:52.591
So before he blew
his brains out,

09:52.593 --> 09:54.960
He took a hammer and
smashed both of his hands.

09:54.962 --> 09:56.461
The hands of a surgeon.

09:56.463 --> 09:58.930
They were his most
valuable possession.
Oh, god...

09:58.932 --> 10:01.199
What am I gonna do now?

10:01.201 --> 10:04.069
You're gonna get out, before
I call the cops.
Oh, come...
Just a minute...

10:04.071 --> 10:05.337
Get out, you freaks!

10:10.276 --> 10:12.744
Oh, ho, ho! Okay.

10:12.746 --> 10:14.779
Whoa...

10:16.616 --> 10:18.683
(chuckles)

10:21.320 --> 10:23.455
Huh.

10:23.457 --> 10:25.390
(grunts)

10:27.126 --> 10:29.995
Hey, it's the strong man.

10:29.997 --> 10:31.396
I keep trying
with this thing

10:31.398 --> 10:33.131
And I can't even
get it halfway up.

10:33.133 --> 10:34.966
I feel like
a damn fairy.

10:34.968 --> 10:36.968
Hey, don't be cute, buddy.

10:36.970 --> 10:39.137
I'm in the mood
to hurt someone today,

10:39.139 --> 10:41.506
And trust me, you don't
want it to be you.
What's the matter?

10:41.508 --> 10:44.042
You can't actually
get it up?

10:53.352 --> 10:55.487
(bell dings)

10:57.023 --> 10:58.490
Well, I'll be.

10:58.492 --> 11:00.959
Say, what do you say we go
get a drink and you, uh,

11:00.961 --> 11:02.427
You tell me
your trick?

11:02.429 --> 11:04.462
I know this place a
couple of towns over

11:04.464 --> 11:06.531
Called, uh...
High noon.

11:07.767 --> 11:09.467
What?

11:09.469 --> 11:11.670
Oh! You-you haven't
heard of it?

11:11.672 --> 11:15.173
Why, that's funny, because
I saw you there today.

11:15.175 --> 11:17.642
And so did a lot of
other people, I'm sure.

11:17.644 --> 11:19.844
You were pretty upset
about one of those,

11:19.846 --> 11:23.682
Uh, sweet little things
that works there.

11:23.684 --> 11:25.050
Maggie:
What's going on, fellas?

11:27.219 --> 11:29.120
Kind of hard
to hit the bell

11:29.122 --> 11:30.789
When richard's in
your way, isn't it?

11:30.791 --> 11:33.091
You might
hit him instead.

11:35.194 --> 11:39.164
Ah, these things are
rigged anyway, right?

11:39.166 --> 11:42.067
Dell and I are gonna
head into the tent
to chat, instead.

11:42.069 --> 11:44.436
You got it.

11:47.907 --> 11:50.575
Rule number one.

11:50.577 --> 11:53.878
When attempting to blackmail
a man with freakish strength

11:53.880 --> 11:55.980
And a mean streak the
size of the panhandle,

11:55.982 --> 11:57.449
Make sure you
got witnesses.

12:08.360 --> 12:10.829
Stanley:
You're my ideal man.

12:10.831 --> 12:12.864
And I'm not talking about
your bulging muscles.

12:12.866 --> 12:14.566
Though I have
to admit--

12:14.568 --> 12:17.235
For someone so strong, you
lack the beefcake look.

12:17.237 --> 12:19.671
No.

12:19.673 --> 12:21.740
You have the three qualities
I love in a person.

12:21.742 --> 12:23.708
One-- you lack a moral code.

12:23.710 --> 12:26.177
Two-- you can kill a man
with your bare hands.

12:26.179 --> 12:28.079
And three-- you have
to do whatever I say,

12:28.081 --> 12:29.914
Or I'm gonna make sure
this whole place knows

12:29.916 --> 12:32.350
That you have someone else's
shit under your fingernails.

12:32.352 --> 12:33.952
Oh, I'm gonna kill you.

12:33.954 --> 12:35.220
Not now, you won't.

12:35.222 --> 12:37.255
Maggie saw us
come in here.

12:37.257 --> 12:39.090
And not later.

12:39.092 --> 12:40.892
'cause I'm very good
with this thing.

12:40.894 --> 12:43.261
I like to aim
for the jewels.

12:43.263 --> 12:45.130
Kind of my
signature shot.

12:45.132 --> 12:46.698
The screams of the men
who have been nut-shot

12:46.700 --> 12:48.032
Are so specific.

12:48.034 --> 12:50.902
Came here to make a deal, right?

12:50.904 --> 12:52.971
Talk.

13:01.981 --> 13:04.048
I need one of your freaks.

13:04.050 --> 13:05.650
Dead.

13:05.652 --> 13:08.920
Keep it clean, I want
the body intact.

13:08.922 --> 13:11.990
And it needs to look like
they just disappeared.

13:16.462 --> 13:18.563
You want me to kill
one of my own?

13:18.565 --> 13:21.199
I weep from your sudden
sentimentality.

13:26.939 --> 13:31.176
There's a barn a couple of miles
due west of here.

13:31.178 --> 13:33.178
Bring the body there.

13:37.449 --> 13:38.950
You've got a day.

13:38.952 --> 13:41.019
(whistles casually)

13:43.789 --> 13:46.024
Maggie:
<i>What's on your mind?</i>

13:46.026 --> 13:49.027
You're a million miles
away tonight.
(doo-wop song plays)

13:49.029 --> 13:50.995
I was just thinking
about the twins.

13:50.997 --> 13:52.764
How they changed
their story.

13:52.766 --> 13:55.767
Made me look like a fool
in front of everybody.

13:55.769 --> 13:57.769
Maybe they got confused.

13:57.771 --> 14:01.172
No, there's something weird
going on around here.

14:01.174 --> 14:05.176
I don't know what, but it's
got my head all screwed up.

14:05.178 --> 14:07.045
Maybe it's
another sign.

14:07.047 --> 14:08.446
That it's time
for us to go.

14:08.448 --> 14:11.616
We could leave right now,
before the sun comes up.

14:11.618 --> 14:13.952
Unless you changed
your mind...

14:13.954 --> 14:15.954
No, of course not.

14:15.956 --> 14:17.488
I'll go with you.

14:17.490 --> 14:18.857
Then let's go.

14:18.859 --> 14:19.991
Right now.

14:19.993 --> 14:21.025
I can't right now.

14:21.027 --> 14:23.461
It doesn't feel right.

14:23.463 --> 14:25.163
That rich kid,

14:25.165 --> 14:28.833
You should have seen the way
he was looking at the twins.

14:28.835 --> 14:30.835
And that second clown--

14:30.837 --> 14:34.239
Do you think you would recognize
his voice if you heard it?

14:34.241 --> 14:35.807
I-I don't know.

14:35.809 --> 14:37.709
He was... He was wearing
that mask.

14:37.711 --> 14:40.011
And it's over.

14:40.013 --> 14:41.246
Why does it matter?

14:41.248 --> 14:44.015
Because justice
is justice.

14:44.017 --> 14:46.017
That guy almost
sawed you in half.

14:46.019 --> 14:48.319
If the rich kid did
it, he has to pay.

14:50.256 --> 14:52.257
You know
what I think?

14:52.259 --> 14:54.259
You're stalling.

14:54.261 --> 14:56.261
No, I'm not.

14:56.263 --> 14:58.263
I want to go.

14:58.265 --> 15:01.032
I just need a few more days
to get everything in order.

15:01.034 --> 15:03.034
That's bullshit.

15:03.036 --> 15:05.036
You're never gonna
leave this place.

15:05.038 --> 15:08.039
¶ you knew when you loved me

15:08.041 --> 15:12.343
¶ I never would resist...

15:26.125 --> 15:28.192
¶

15:50.082 --> 15:53.051
¶ I never would resist...

15:55.087 --> 15:57.655
You trying
to get with me?

15:58.924 --> 16:01.492
¶ I'll give in...

16:01.494 --> 16:03.494
Don't make this difficult now.

16:03.496 --> 16:04.629
(screams)
goddamn it!

16:05.965 --> 16:09.100
¶ my only sin

16:09.102 --> 16:11.736
¶ but the same guided missiles

16:11.738 --> 16:17.175
¶ will get you in the end...

16:20.012 --> 16:21.479
(screams)

16:21.481 --> 16:23.481
All right, all right,
uncle, uncle.

16:23.483 --> 16:27.251
¶ but the same guided missiles

16:27.253 --> 16:33.257
¶ will get you in the...

16:33.259 --> 16:36.194
¶ end.

16:36.196 --> 16:38.329
Who's the strong man now?

16:47.272 --> 16:48.940
Amazon eve:
And all I can think about is

16:48.942 --> 16:50.341
His grubby hands
all over me.

16:50.343 --> 16:51.776
(groans)

16:51.778 --> 16:53.478
No, keep your
hand on ice.

16:53.480 --> 16:55.847
Your swelling will
never go down.
Ugh.

16:55.849 --> 16:58.449
Dell's done a lot
of rotten things, but this?

16:58.451 --> 17:00.885
He must be out
of his mind.

17:00.887 --> 17:02.053
We got to get
our facts straight,

17:02.055 --> 17:02.987
So when we go to the cops...

17:02.989 --> 17:05.456
Cops?

17:05.458 --> 17:07.458
You of all people saying that.

17:07.460 --> 17:09.694
Dell is our problem;
we're gonna fix it.

17:09.696 --> 17:12.964
We're gonna sneak into
his trailer, kill him.

17:12.966 --> 17:14.399
What?! Whoa, whoa!

17:14.401 --> 17:15.867
Ma, where's this coming from?

17:15.869 --> 17:17.568
I know him, jimmy.

17:17.570 --> 17:19.170
I know what
he's capable of.

17:19.172 --> 17:20.405
And you don't.

17:20.407 --> 17:23.007
Jesus, ma, well,
at least let me talk to him.

17:23.009 --> 17:24.542
Amazon eve: What if
he'd come after maggie?

17:24.544 --> 17:26.911
You'd be the first one
charging in with a gun.

17:26.913 --> 17:28.479
Suzi: You don't know
what it's like,

17:28.481 --> 17:30.148
Peepers flipping up our skirts.

17:30.150 --> 17:31.916
Ethel: You know what
your problem is, jimmy?

17:31.918 --> 17:34.018
You're stuck on the rosy notion

17:34.020 --> 17:37.021
That the world operates
on goodness,

17:37.023 --> 17:39.323
Decency.

17:39.325 --> 17:41.325
Truth is--

17:41.327 --> 17:43.327
All goodness guarantees ya...

17:43.329 --> 17:46.130
Is an early grave.

17:48.167 --> 17:51.035
But the biggest joke of all--

17:51.037 --> 17:54.105
The thing that'll sink ya
every time...

17:56.041 --> 17:58.109
...Is hope.

18:01.180 --> 18:05.116
Hope that the world
will right itself.

18:05.118 --> 18:09.187
That the just will be rewarded
and the wicked punished.

18:12.424 --> 18:15.093
Oh, once you buy into
that horseshit,

18:15.095 --> 18:17.195
You're dead in the water.

18:17.197 --> 18:20.398
The only way to survive

18:20.400 --> 18:23.668
In this disgusting
godforsaken world...

18:25.604 --> 18:27.605
