35:39.004 --> 35:40.604
Elsa,

35:40.606 --> 35:44.174
You can be the fairy godmother
who grants the wish

35:44.176 --> 35:46.009
Of the plain jane--
that's dot--

35:46.011 --> 35:48.111
And transforms her into
the epitome of glamour.

35:48.113 --> 35:50.313
That's me.

35:50.315 --> 35:53.416
Well, how kind of you to include
me in your number, huh?

35:53.418 --> 35:55.118
Oh, you wave the wand,
that's all you do.

35:55.120 --> 35:58.088
Well, I'll go to work on it
right away.

35:58.090 --> 36:01.191
Let me know if there's anything
else you might want.

36:02.994 --> 36:04.528
I'm making a list.

36:04.530 --> 36:06.997
Oh...

36:06.999 --> 36:10.133
Gladys, I think the hair
is too poofy on that side.

36:10.135 --> 36:12.903
Don't push too hard now.

36:28.286 --> 36:30.020
Elsa:
<i>"my dear dot.</i>

36:30.022 --> 36:33.523
"you hardly said a word
during our negotiation,

36:33.525 --> 36:37.160
"until you demanded
your 50%.

36:37.162 --> 36:39.863
"what would you want
with the money,

36:39.865 --> 36:41.831
"a bigger tent?

36:41.833 --> 36:43.533
"a new car?

36:43.535 --> 36:46.469
"just tell me
your heart's desire.

36:46.471 --> 36:49.673
"you can trust me
to help you.

36:49.675 --> 36:52.509
"we are in this together.

36:52.511 --> 36:54.110
Elsa."

36:57.181 --> 36:59.983
(gentle melody plays)

36:59.985 --> 37:01.384
(singsongy):
Miss elsa?

37:01.386 --> 37:03.320
What do you want, <i>liebchen?</i>

37:04.889 --> 37:05.922
Here, darling.

37:05.924 --> 37:08.058
Make mama another one, okay?

37:08.060 --> 37:09.326
(kisses)

37:09.328 --> 37:10.860
The usual.

37:10.862 --> 37:15.031
¶ doesn't shine for us all

37:15.033 --> 37:18.835
¶ always remember
where twilight descent ¶

37:18.837 --> 37:21.071
Dot:
"yes. I want something.

37:21.073 --> 37:22.939
"there's a doctor in chicago

37:22.941 --> 37:24.908
"who separated
the brodie twins.

37:24.910 --> 37:27.277
"his name is
dr. Oscar sugar.

37:27.279 --> 37:29.279
"I want you to
help me find him

37:29.281 --> 37:31.915
"and convince him to
perform the surgery.

37:31.917 --> 37:35.051
Your secret is safe as long
as I get what I want."

37:35.053 --> 37:37.287
¶ hold the key to your heart

37:37.289 --> 37:40.924
¶ don't be afraid of what all

37:40.926 --> 37:43.126
¶ that extends
<i>danke.</i>

37:43.128 --> 37:46.963
¶ loneliness ends with love.

37:46.965 --> 37:48.565
(needle buzzing)

37:48.567 --> 37:50.600
You're too much
of a perfectionist.

37:50.602 --> 37:52.269
Morris:
Well, I have to be.

37:52.271 --> 37:55.705
There can be no mistakes.

37:55.707 --> 37:59.276
You see, human skin
is a delicate canvas.

37:59.278 --> 38:02.912
Uneven, textured,

38:02.914 --> 38:04.781
Sometimes scarred.

38:04.783 --> 38:07.384
(needle buzzing)
and she...

38:07.386 --> 38:09.085
She is my masterpiece.

38:09.087 --> 38:11.388
And she's waking up.

38:11.390 --> 38:13.556
Where's a mirror?
Right there.

38:13.558 --> 38:16.826
I want to see the look
on her face.

38:20.097 --> 38:23.600
¶ penny, penny,
open your eyes ¶

38:23.602 --> 38:26.636
¶ daddy's got a
big surprise. ¶

38:26.638 --> 38:29.172
Penny (whining):
Daddy, it hurts.

38:29.174 --> 38:31.007
(crying):
It hurts.

38:31.009 --> 38:34.210
Beauty is painful, sweetheart.

38:36.847 --> 38:38.448
(screaming)

38:38.450 --> 38:40.016
Vince: Stick out your tongue.

38:40.018 --> 38:42.085
(laughing)
I had it forked.

38:42.087 --> 38:43.019
(screaming)

38:51.028 --> 38:52.162
¶

38:52.164 --> 38:53.997
Stanley:
So...

38:53.999 --> 38:55.799
It's true what they say.

38:55.801 --> 38:57.901
Stars really don't eat.

39:00.171 --> 39:02.339
Okay, so let's get down
to business.

39:02.341 --> 39:04.841
I have a problem.

39:04.843 --> 39:06.876
A serious situation.

39:06.878 --> 39:08.144
The twins are back.

39:08.146 --> 39:11.281
Not only are they back,
but they are

39:11.283 --> 39:13.116
Hell-bent on destroying me.

39:14.352 --> 39:17.887
Now, little miss sour face--

39:17.889 --> 39:20.156
That's dot...
Ah.

39:20.158 --> 39:22.225
...She wants to locate

39:22.227 --> 39:25.128
A doctor in chicago

39:25.130 --> 39:27.063
Whom she believes

39:27.065 --> 39:30.467
Can perform some
hideous operation.

39:30.469 --> 39:34.571
What I want to do is have
you locate this doctor

39:34.573 --> 39:37.640
And then we could send
them up to chicago.

39:37.642 --> 39:39.743
They will be out of my life,

39:39.745 --> 39:42.645
Off my back forever.

39:42.647 --> 39:44.013
Do you, uh...

39:44.015 --> 39:47.050
Oh, no, go ahead.

39:47.052 --> 39:48.017
Please, be my guest.

39:48.019 --> 39:50.720
(grunts)

39:50.722 --> 39:52.155
Just mulling.

39:52.157 --> 39:55.225
This is good brain food,
red meat.

39:55.227 --> 39:57.227
(growls)

40:02.933 --> 40:05.502
I don't know.

40:07.171 --> 40:08.938
Perhaps rather than
some medical calamity,

40:08.940 --> 40:10.373
Which they believe
is going to relieve them

40:10.375 --> 40:11.941
Of their psychic pain,

40:11.943 --> 40:15.512
Something more simple
and less public.

40:15.514 --> 40:18.515
Maybe life holds too much pain

40:18.517 --> 40:20.083
And tragedy
for those poor girls.

40:20.085 --> 40:22.085
Wouldn't it be a better solution

40:22.087 --> 40:25.054
If they could be quietly
and easily relieved

40:25.056 --> 40:26.523
Of their misery?

40:26.525 --> 40:28.057
What are you saying?

40:28.059 --> 40:29.559
You know...

40:29.561 --> 40:32.061
A mercy killing.
(sharp laugh)

40:32.063 --> 40:34.431
Those poor things.

40:34.433 --> 40:36.299
(laughs)

40:36.301 --> 40:37.934
Oh, that's quite a solution.

40:37.936 --> 40:40.203
Yeah.

40:41.272 --> 40:44.441
Did you know they killed
their mother?

40:44.443 --> 40:46.743
(grunts)
and then one of them

40:46.745 --> 40:48.478
Tried to kill the other.

40:48.480 --> 40:50.046
I forget which is which--
the two...

40:50.048 --> 40:51.848
Ethel:
Dessert time.

40:53.384 --> 40:55.952
My layered strawberry
and lime jell-o mold

40:55.954 --> 40:57.987
With marshmallows
and fruit cocktail.

40:57.989 --> 41:00.290
I'll put it right over here.

41:00.292 --> 41:02.325
You guys can serve yourselves.

41:02.327 --> 41:04.093
Can I get rid of some of this?

41:04.095 --> 41:06.463
Um...

41:06.465 --> 41:08.731
You're a regular betty crocker,
ethel.

41:08.733 --> 41:10.633
You're too kind.

41:10.635 --> 41:12.735
Enjoy.

41:14.738 --> 41:17.173
(grunts)

41:23.013 --> 41:25.014
Well...

41:25.016 --> 41:27.417
Anyway.

41:27.419 --> 41:29.919
(short laugh)

41:31.822 --> 41:34.157
You know...

41:34.159 --> 41:36.960
I have heard about managers

41:36.962 --> 41:40.096
Who would kill
for their clients.

41:41.131 --> 41:44.167
Looks like I found one. Hmm?

41:44.169 --> 41:46.703
(laughing)

42:00.451 --> 42:02.819
(quietly): Ma petite.

42:02.821 --> 42:04.587
Ma petite.

42:08.459 --> 42:10.527
For you.

42:10.529 --> 42:13.229
Would you like me
to open it?

42:22.339 --> 42:24.140
(gasps)

42:24.142 --> 42:25.675
Pretty.

42:25.677 --> 42:29.913
I can't wait to try it on.

42:29.915 --> 42:31.714
(chuckles softly)

42:52.036 --> 42:54.170
Zip me.

43:03.347 --> 43:05.214
Gorgeous.

43:05.216 --> 43:06.583
Like a little princess.

43:06.585 --> 43:09.319
Thank you.

43:17.061 --> 43:19.028
(bones crunching,
ma petite whimpering)

43:19.030 --> 43:20.063
Shh...

43:20.065 --> 43:22.198
(muffled shouting)
shh...

43:22.200 --> 43:24.100
It's going to be all right.

43:24.102 --> 43:26.002
(muffled screams)

43:26.937 --> 43:29.305
(bones crunching)

43:29.307 --> 43:30.707
(muffled screaming)

43:30.709 --> 43:32.976
(screaming stops)

43:36.480 --> 43:39.649
(sighs)

43:41.151 --> 43:43.353
(quietly):
I'm sorry.

43:50.394 --> 43:52.962
(creaking)

43:55.065 --> 43:56.666
(creaking continues)

43:56.668 --> 43:58.167
(yells)

44:00.671 --> 44:02.472
Hello?

44:02.474 --> 44:04.641
Who's there?

44:05.809 --> 44:07.510
Show yourself.

44:07.512 --> 44:10.146
Now!

44:21.992 --> 44:23.693
Penny.

44:27.631 --> 44:30.033
Oh, god.

44:30.035 --> 44:32.035
This is my fault.

44:33.203 --> 44:34.837
What have I done?

44:34.839 --> 44:37.106
Oh.

44:37.108 --> 44:39.108
(crying)

44:43.047 --> 44:45.415
(low conversations)

44:51.155 --> 44:52.955
(glass clinking)

44:52.957 --> 44:56.025
Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen.

44:56.027 --> 44:58.795
Our esteemed board members

44:58.797 --> 45:02.065
And our renowned faculty.

45:02.067 --> 45:06.135
Tonight, we are proud to unveil
the museum's latest acquisition.

45:06.137 --> 45:08.071
A most rare specimen.

45:08.073 --> 45:10.807
And while it did cost
a pretty penny,

45:10.809 --> 45:12.575
We trust that this new exhibit

45:12.577 --> 45:16.345
Will bring <i>thousands</i>
<i>of visitors</i>

45:16.347 --> 45:18.081
From around the globe.

45:18.083 --> 45:20.083
Behold.

45:20.085 --> 45:21.851
Mahadevi patel.

45:21.853 --> 45:24.153
(partygoers gasping)

45:24.155 --> 45:27.156
The smallest woman
in the world.

45:27.158 --> 45:29.225
(murmuring)

